reviews.text: Such a great place to go for breakfast for brunch. I have celiac disease and brought a friend and she could not even tell that the food was gluten-free. Amazing place! Try the mini cinnamon roll!

Excellent gluten-free restaurant. The lemon waffle was seriously delicious, light and fluffy with lemon curd and whipped cream! Yum. I got some scrambled eggs and bacon on the side for protein. The eggs could have been better since they were cracked and scrambled on the grill. A little overcooked too. But I was focused on my waffle. My husband liked his breakfast sandwich too.
I was a little disappointed that they didn't have decaf coffee, but we enjoyed our breakfast.
Note that you order at the counter and sit wherever. Comfy, family style seating.

I love this place. Never had a bad experience, I‚Äôve loved every menu single item I‚Äôve had. The entire place is gluten free and they have an entire dairy free and vegan menu as well. They also serve drinks and desserts. Depending on the time you go, there can be a long wait or no wait. I‚Äôm obsessed with their breakfast fries and banana French toast sticks. They have an entire separate dinner menu on certain days, check their business hours on their social media for those times.

Excellent experience here! The food was delicious and the menu wasn't overwhelming. So many tasty options for sweet and savory. The Chicken and waffles was even bigger than I expected it to be and I was thrilled about that! The space is super cute and just fun and relaxing to be in.
Tacos (pictured) were fabulous too as well as my bagel sandwich. And the prices seemed right.
I will definitely be back!

This place is great! Incredibly gluten-friendly, which is amazing considering most of the menu is very bread-heavy options. Allergies of them were delicious, the waffles and the bagel sandwich were standouts. The sweet roll was good, but a bit more grainy and crumbly than a gluten cinnamon roll. The seating situation is a bit cramped; we came on a snowy morning, but it was still busy. We had to sit at a larger table with another group at the other end. Not terrible, but be aware. It is just a small restaurant. Neither of us have gluten allergies, but have relatives who are, and we will definitely be taking them here when they come to visit!

detailedReviews.author: dreamynation
detailedReviews.text:
Food is yummy, and it came out quick. Forgot the name of my drink, but it was great too. Really nice place to have breakfast. The only complaint was that the bench seats along the wall weren't really comfortable to sit.

Still recommend to visit for the food :)

detailedReviews.author: Amanda Lillywhite
detailedReviews.text: Yummy gluten free breakfast!

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Charter
detailedReviews.text: The place is alright. The food wasn't that great for the cost. There are places with comparable prices and better tasting food. They do counter service but if you get a drink, you have to get up and go to the counter and wait for someone else to refill it. Lastly, their kitchen isn't very well ventilated. It was slightly smoky out in the dining area due to cooking in the back, and that wasn't great. It's an okay spot for breakfast but there are better options at the same price point.

detailedReviews.author: Brooke Anderson
detailedReviews.text: They have GF mozzarella sticks! Love this place for GF options but not too thrilled about their hours.

detailedReviews.author: Melanie Merrill
detailedReviews.text: I love locals!!!! The food is delicious, everyone is so nice, and they gave me a sweet roll on my birthday! All my friends say the food doesn't taste gluten free. As someone with celiac disease, this is the best place to eat in Utah county. I come here at least twice a month. Everything on the menu is delicious!

detailedReviews.author: Michaela Bratcher
detailedReviews.text: Food was fantastic. I got the spicy sweet chili chicken and waffles. Waffles were so soft with outer crunch and the chicken was immaculate. Great place for gluten and dairy free options. Black coffee was divine as well. Will definitely be returning!

detailedReviews.author: Maria Jaroslaw Sautter
detailedReviews.text: GLUTEN FREE CHICKEN AND WAFFLES, are you kidding me?! I wish I could eat it every day, it‚Äôs so good.

detailedReviews.author: Jacob Shaffer
detailedReviews.text:
A rarely give reviews. The food was good, no complaints there. The service not so much. If people want to go out for brunch on a Sunday then do chores for someone else‚Äôs business, this is the place for you!

I had to go up and order myself the food I wanted, pour my own drinks, and then clean up my own table after I was done. All this after I tipped them before I even got my food.

To top it all off, when my wife asked for a to-go box she got a snarky attitude for asking. She obviously ‚Äúinterrupted‚Äù some super ‚Äúinteresting‚Äù conversation the co-workers were having! Our mistake!!

If I could revoke the tip I gave, I would. NEVER eating here again. ‚úåüèº

detailedReviews.author: Brandon Rutan
detailedReviews.text: Just for starters $80 for a simple breakfast for 3 in outrageous. Let alone it being extremely dirty, unprofessional environment I.E. it felt like I was eating at a commune not a restaurant in downtown Provo. Every plate was chipped in multiple places. The chairs felt like they were ready to fall apart, the choisons were littered with stains, the employees looked the part of a hippie commune.

detailedReviews.author: Adelyn
detailedReviews.text: Overpriced and mediocre food. Our food was plated on extremely chipped and broken plates. The tables and seats were dirty, and the kitchen looked dirty as well. On top of being dirty, the seating was awkward. Predominately large tables so it felt a little odd sitting with 2-3 other groups. The prices were absolutely ABSURD! We spent nearly $80 on a basic breakfast for three. I get having a gluten-friendly place sounds amazing but not for the price. As a gluten-free chef myself, I wouldn‚Äôt be happy serving that quality and service to my clients.

detailedReviews.author: sean bandley
detailedReviews.text: Great place for breakfast

detailedReviews.author: Holly Walker

I had breakfast tacos and enjoyed every bite. Loved the rating buffalo sauce with just enough kick to perfectly finish off the tacos. Definitely a must-try for any GF foodie!

detailedReviews.author: Alex Mospanyuk
detailedReviews.text: Not great. Overpriced.

detailedReviews.author: giselle

I paid $40 for 2 items and a side. The hash browns were cold when they came out, and the portions were underwhelming. My expectations were high because of the reviews but me and my party were completely disappointed. Money down the drain, honestly wish that I had asked for a refund because it was so badüëé

detailedReviews.text: From out of town, but I will be back for this place!! Breakfast tacosüî• banana fosters pancakesüî• deep fried banana bread sticksüî•üî• and all gluten free!!

detailedReviews.author: Sabrina Joyner
detailedReviews.text: It's awesome to be able to go to a place where I can eat all the menu items. I had the lemon pound cake waffle and it was soooo good!!!

detailedReviews.author: Matt Peterson
detailedReviews.text: Best Gluten Free food in the valley! Dairy free is also an option. I love the chicken and waffles, the breakfast sandwich, and the bakery muffins and mini cakes!

detailedReviews.author: Hunter Bartley
detailedReviews.text: One of the best new restaurants in Utah County. A bit pricey, but worth it. Come hungry. Their caramel sauce is divine.

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Flinders
detailedReviews.text: Delicious and gluten free!

detailedReviews.author: Sandra McCollum
detailedReviews.text: Breakfast tacos and pancakes are so good. Great portion size. Everything we have tried is delicious.

detailedReviews.author: Eyes Open
detailedReviews.text:
BREAKFAST TACOS: delicious.  Kids didn‚Äôt want them.

BAGEL SANDWICH: dry gluten free bagel.  Without bacon it‚Äôs flavorless.  Too much fat with tons of cream cheese, avocado and eggs.  Nauseating to eat after a while.

BACON, LITTLE PANCAKES & EGGS: substituted hashbrowns patties for bacon.  Kids liked it.  Too much caramel sauce.  Was supposed to be drizzled with it but it was smothered.

Lots of smoke.  One door was propped open a couple inches but we opened both and propped them open a lot.  Took a long time to get our food.

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Duncan
detailedReviews.text: Been here multiple times and it never disappoints!! Consistently delicious and great service.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Braman
detailedReviews.text: My kids and I were looking for a brunch spot, and Locals popped up on Google Maps. We had a fantastic experience‚Äîthe staff was warm and welcoming, the food was delicious, and the atmosphere was cozy and inviting. We‚Äôll definitely be back! Highly recommended.

detailedReviews.author: Melissa Neary
detailedReviews.text: Absolutely some of the best gluten free food I‚Äôve tasted since being diagnosed with celiacs. It felt so nice to eat ‚Äúnormally‚Äù for a breakfast.

detailedReviews.author: Kyme Lambson
detailedReviews.text: Great service, fun ambiance. You'll be sad about the gluten free elements, but you'll feel comfortable and at ease as you shed a tear or two at flavors missed.

detailedReviews.author: charlotte85 *
detailedReviews.text:
We've had the pancakes, waffles and chicken, breakfast tacos, loaded fries with and without chicken, the cinnamon roll, lemon pound cake waffle for breakfast and we've also tried the dinner salad and waffle sandwich, loaded fries as well as the kids meals for Mac and cheese. Obviously we've eaten here a lot ü§£
It's been super awesome for my husband to be able to get a really good fried chicken and waffle that's GF.  And I absolutely love their house sauce on the load of fries and the breakfast tacos are incredible! The consistency of a lot of the pancakes/waffles etc are incredible. And it's such a friendly atmosphere.
Jesse the owner is just the best and works so hard to provide a great and safe place. Highly recommend.

detailedReviews.author: Megan Farris
detailedReviews.text: Such a relaxing environment and some great quality food! Their coffee and waffles are delicious. And they have so many vegan options!

detailedReviews.author: Heather Kofoed
detailedReviews.text: This is a celiac safe restaurant. All the food here is gluten free which is so nice! The food I got was good, not mind blowing or anything it had a taste of oil which threw me off, I would go back and try other things. They did recently add dinner options. The only tricky thing about them is weird hours because they are such a specialty restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Spencer
detailedReviews.text:
While I had high hopes for my visit to Local, my experience left much to be desired. The food was fine, but I was disappointed to find that the prices listed online were lower than what I encountered in person. For instance, I was charged an extra $4 to add chicken to my dish, which turned out to be a very small portion.

Additionally, my coffee was $5, and unfortunately, the lid popped off immediately, spilling all over me. This was not only inconvenient but also quite messy.

Overall, I wouldn't return to this restaurant. They need to address their pricing discrepancies, improve the quality of their ingredients, and definitely fix their coffee lids.

detailedReviews.author: Joshua Gibb
detailedReviews.text: Do not order to-go from this restaurant. I ordered the banana Foster‚Äôs pancakes and receive two small, thin pancakes that looked like they came from McDonalds, maybe two tablespoons of cream, and syrup. A complete waste of money.

detailedReviews.author: Natalie Gray
detailedReviews.text: There are no vegan options. The reviews are wrong, but the customer service was great even though they had break my heart on vegan pancakes.

detailedReviews.author: Liv Alder
detailedReviews.text:
If I could leave zero stars for the food, I would. I was thrilled to see a unique menu, but everything fell short. The first three items I wanted to order they were out of, so I was already off to a rocky start. I settled for the French toast sticks and the breakfast tacos. The French toast sticks were overcooked and crunchy, making them inedible. The breakfast tacos came with avocado on it. When it came out, there was no avocado, and the hashbrowns on the tacos were burnt.
Staff was incredibly friendly but disorganized. I was really looking forward to this place, but left disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Aubrielle Miner
detailedReviews.text: 100% dedicated gluten-free restaurant with dairy free options!! Basically heaven if you have food allergies. I avoid coming here on Saturdays because they are packed. The staff is very kind and I love the food! Some things are better than others, (fried banana bread is to die for, but I‚Äôve had better GF cinnamon rolls). Honestly I just love being able to go to a restaurant and not have to ask a million questions about the menu and what is or isn‚Äôt GF. And for being allergy friendly I am very pleased with the prices! I have paid way more for way less at other places. They‚Äôre a pretty new establishment so they‚Äôre still working out some kinks and building the business, but I hope they start having more hours during the week! And a lunch menu!!

detailedReviews.author: Brandon Dalley
detailedReviews.text: My wife and daughter have celiac and my son has a dairy allergy so needless to say finding anywhere that serves breakfast that caters to this is very challenging. I have no allergy issues so even with the places that do have options for them I rarely enjoy the food. Locals is not only the exception, I prefer their food over non allergy friendly places. The food was spectacular. The breakfast tacos are the best I have ever had at any eatery. The bananas foster pancakes were exceptional. To add to this they make an excellent latte. Completely blown away. I never write reviews but the food was so fantastic I want to do anything I can to encourage business (because selfishly I want one to open closer to where we live so I can frequent their business lol). Go here, celiac or not. You will not be disappointed. In the mean time I‚Äôll be dreaming about the breakfast tacos until I make the 40 minutes drive again.

detailedReviews.author: Paul Durant
detailedReviews.text: Seating was sparse but that was also just the time of day. In general, the food was underwhelming. The banana foster pancake was just a pancake with syrup and bananas which was fine but nothing impressive. The bacon was almost burnt and the eggs were fried to the point of having the yolk dry. Nothing bad but also nothing really great.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Seabrook
detailedReviews.text: Well, folks, they've done it again, but this time it's now dinner time, and the chicken and waffle sandwiches hit the spot 100%. This is a must try dinner spot..

detailedReviews.author: Courtney Rasband
detailedReviews.text: I would have thought they weren‚Äôt Gluten Free chicken and waffles if I wasn‚Äôt at a dedicated restaurant. The waffles were tender and crispy too! The flavors were so good! We also had the breakfast tacos. They did not disappoint either! I will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: S√≥focles Mor√°n
detailedReviews.text: Really good, every single detail!

detailedReviews.author: Quincy Haslam
detailedReviews.text: My husband and I came here on a whim. It did not disappoint! Excellent service and even better food.

detailedReviews.text:
Excellent experience here! The food was delicious and the menu wasn't overwhelming. So many tasty options for sweet and savory. The Chicken and waffles was even bigger than I expected it to be and I was thrilled about that! The space is super cute and just fun and relaxing to be in.
Tacos (pictured) were fabulous too as well as my bagel sandwich. And the prices seemed right.
I will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Casey Anderson
detailedReviews.text: This place was outstanding! They were able to accommodate a party of 25 last minute and handled it with ease! We received our food in a timely manner and it was absolutely delicious! You can tell that everything is home made and fresh. I will recommend this place to anyone I know visiting Provo!

detailedReviews.author: Erik Hight
detailedReviews.text: I went here for breakfast on a Sunday. Excellent food and excellent service. Best gluten free cinnamon roll I've ever had!

detailedReviews.author: Bill Miller
detailedReviews.text: They have updated the interior to a very nice warm atmosphere. As far as the food goes, it is still as delicious as the first time that we came. My wife absolutely loves the fact that she can get a lemon curd waffle with whipped topping that is not only Gluten-Free but dairy free as well. Of course I had the giant cinnamon roll covered in dairy-free caramel sauce. Now I don't have a problem with gluten or dairy but, when in Rome.... My Gluten-Free cinnamon roll covered in delicious dairy-free caramel sauce was absolutely delicious. If you haven't tried them out you need to do it.

detailedReviews.author: RAJ
detailedReviews.text:
Delicious! Gluten free brunch.
We got the breakfast tacos, a sweet roll, and some mini pancakes. All good!
I'd love to go back and try the Banana Bread Sticks and Chicken and Waffles...

detailedReviews.author: Faye Johnson
detailedReviews.text: My mom and I (both GF) love this place so much!! So fun to be able to eat out together and enjoy some BOMB gluten free food. We like the banana French toast sticks and the chicken and waffles the best. They are so cheap as well too for gluten free. We will praise locals to the skies to anyone who will hear us!! üì£üì£

detailedReviews.author: Lake Fett
detailedReviews.text: Incredibly authentic and genuine and heartful owner. He deserves all the business in the world simply for how he conducts himself in the real world and his generousity. ‚ù§Ô∏è

detailedReviews.author: Alyssa Holbrook
detailedReviews.text: Sooo good and such nice employees. The food is to die for!!! (And u won‚Äôt die either if you‚Äôre celiac)

detailedReviews.author: Alejandra Gimenez
detailedReviews.text:
I really wanted to like this place but they unfortunately fell short. I ordered the fried banana bread sticks because lots of other reviews have raved about it. Mine was completely burnt--like, completely blackened and I could only cut off maybe 1/3 of each piece to eat. I had to use a fork and knife to cut through and it took work. I think the idea is great but execution was poor. Also it was served on way too small of a plate--syrup was falling off all over the place. My husband ordered pancakes and they were burnt on one side as well, and his bacon was underdone. We asked for our money back because it truly wasn't edible and they were nice about it.

They were busy, but for me that should never be an excuse for poor food service. The mark of a good versus a great place is one that can produce the same quality regardless of how many people are there.

A smaller comment, but the seating is awkward. They have mainly large tables, so you ended up sharing with at least one other group at your table. It would have been better with a bunch of small tables.

detailedReviews.author: Grace Hansen
detailedReviews.text: Super delicious gluten free brunch!! I had the waffles and they were so good! Will definitely be back. Like other people have said, specialty gluten free stuff like this is usually more expensive and lower quality. It's nice to actually go somewhere with affordable prices and amazing food.

detailedReviews.author: Nathan Worthington
detailedReviews.text: I've heard this place is great, but it's never open. Make sure you scout ahead because it seems like they flip a coin before deciding to open their doors.

detailedReviews.author: Caitlin Kerr
detailedReviews.text: I went to Locals Brunch House on a Wednesday morning and had the place to myself. The food was freshly made to order and I ADORE the GF & DF menu!!! I love having a place that offers delicious options in a celiac-safe environment. I highly recommend the bagel sandwich, but want to eat everything on the menu!

detailedReviews.author: Tizzy P
detailedReviews.text: SO FREAKING GOOD!!!! I can even bring my non-gluten free friends and they love it! And the prices are all REALLY good for gf food! 10/10 recommendation, you‚Äôve got to stop by and try it at least once.

detailedReviews.author: Juan David S√°nchez Aguilar
detailedReviews.text: Very tasty food but very bad service from their American employees we are from Spain and we were today in provo again we went to the restaurant but the treatment was very ugly and apart very rude their employees, before there used to be two very friendly and Latin boys who were very helpful,

detailedReviews.author: Aaron Jensen
detailedReviews.text: This place has some of the best gluten-free options I've ever had!

detailedReviews.author: Amber Peterson
detailedReviews.text: I literally could have made the same food at my home in 10 mins.  We had to ask for utensils, wobbly old chairs to sit on.  Never got my drink I ordered.  We had no idea what time they closed‚Ä¶no hrs listed on doors, anything.  So staff came out and said ‚Äúwe have things to do‚Äù and we were like‚Ä¶sorry, no idea you were closed.  I felt like i was paying to eat at a crappy dorm cafeteria with kids running the place.

detailedReviews.author: Kalae WOods
detailedReviews.text: FOOD WAS SO GOOD! And all Gluten free

detailedReviews.author: Mike Butts
detailedReviews.text: I had breakfast tacos and they were amazing

detailedReviews.author: Rachel Hunter
detailedReviews.text: Great service great employees! Great atmosphere! Great for gluten free!

detailedReviews.author: Melanie Berriman
detailedReviews.text: THE ENTIRE RESTAURANT IS GLUTEN FREE ü§Ø everything I tried was pretty dang good for gluten free, I got the chicken and waffles and my friend got the cinnamon roll and both were really good! detailedReviews.author: Samuel Lewis

This is a very low key well put together spot! The food was phenomenal!

10/10 :)

detailedReviews.author: michael norris
detailedReviews.text: Very good breakfast food. Would highly recommend the fried banana bread sticks. They were superb! Could not even tell it was gluten free.

detailedReviews.author: Jay
detailedReviews.text: We drove out here from Hooper to try out this gluten-free restaurant. We got a bunch of different options. We tried the cinnamon roll, the small pancakes with eggs and bacon, the hot honey chicken and waffles, the lemon pound cake waffle and the bagel sandwich. The cinnamon roll was huge and delicious, we took it home to-go. The winner was the chicken and waffles, my husband was in heaven and I was jealous that I didn't get it for myself. I got the bagel sandwich and was a bit disappointed. It was cold, dry and not what I thought it would be... not enough sauce and moisture and the bagel wasn't toasted. The lemon waffles and pancakes were all fantastic though. There was a huge group there that took all of the chairs and tables when we went so we didn't get a good idea of what the seating is like. Everyone else was squishing together on the benches. The food was worth it though so I'll give them 5 stars for keeping up with the craziness going on that day. My only real complaint was the cold bagel sandwich that came out last after everything else. Definitely get the chicken and waffles or any of the sweet options, they are bomb!

detailedReviews.author: Ethan Strong
detailedReviews.text: This restaurant is exactly what is says: local. Good good food from a local Provo gorl! And even better that I can take my celiac wife here with no anxiety. The food is cheap and if I may: bussin' bussin'. Wouldn't even have thought it was gluten free and celiac friendly.

detailedReviews.author: Kirk Grayam
detailedReviews.text:
Friends recommended this restaurant for their dairy free and gluten free menu.  Food was great was sad to learn we missed out on the dairy free cinnamon rolls.  But otherwise was a great meal. Definitely recommend this to anyone.

Google said they closed at 2pm, but their hours state Wed-Sat 8-4pm

Walked in at 115pm and were told by the staff that was sitting there that they were closed, although there were quite a few customers still in there. Would love to try this place. detailedReviews.author: Russ Madsen
detailedReviews.text: I don‚Äôt eat GF. My GF gf has a hard time at most restaurants so I picked this as a treat/surprise. The staff is so kind, helpful, and patient, not overbearing. I asked them if they could make a demon lovechild between the Bagel Sandwich and Avocado Toast (they were totally willing, even eager to accommodate) with a latte, she got the Bacon Lil Pancakes and Eggs and a Flat White Latte. We shared a Green Smoothie. I don‚Äôt remember ever having a better breakfast sandwich. Excellent flavors, great portions for the price. Very nice atmosphere. Menu is very easy to understand and choose from. For the first time ever I now understand the difference between a latte, cappuccino, and americano thanks to their drink menu.üòä We love this place immediately and plan to come back at least monthly to try everything on the menu. Try it, you‚Äôll love it!

I would‚Äôve given this place 5 stars but the way it‚Äôs ran is wildly disappointing and frustrating

neutral.author: Matthew Charter
neutral.text: The place is alright. The food wasn't that great for the cost. There are places with comparable prices and better tasting food. They do counter service but if you get a drink, you have to get up and go to the counter and wait for someone else to refill it. Lastly, their kitchen isn't very well ventilated. It was slightly smoky out in the dining area due to cooking in the back, and that wasn't great. It's an okay spot for breakfast but there are better options at the same price point.
